13) what are checked and unchecked exceptions in java?

Checked exceptions are the exceptions which are known to compiler. These exceptions are checked at
compile time only. Hence the name checked exceptions. These exceptions are also called compile time exceptions.
Because, these exceptions will be known during compile time.

Unchecked exceptions are those exceptions which are not at all known to compiler.
These exceptions occur only at run time. These exceptions are also called as run time exceptions.
All sub classes of java.lang.RunTimeException and java.lang.Error are unchecked exceptions.